column1: 114093;instagram;2018-12-13 10:48:44;TRUE;;"so about two weeks ago something very unfortunate happened to me.¬†
i was sexually harassed by a trainer at the gym i go to.
at first i was hesitant to write this article
column2: but hopefully it will help other girls/woman on how to deal with similar situations

column1: so basically i trained with this trainer no big deal he was normal and nice and professional. and then after i was done training with him
i won't go into the details of what happened
column2: because that's not what's important here. when it happened tho i felt victimized
column3: i felt betrayed and i felt ashamed.

column1: and all these feelings weren't my fault. it was his fault. i was so upset and unsure of what to do about it. and luckily i have an amazing friend who helped me through this.

column2: i will not just let this go. i decided i will stand up to this guy ( who is in his 40's btw) even though i am only 19.

column1: so long story short i went to the gym's manager
column2: told him what happened ( he was gutted) and he said he will take further steps regarding this matter.

column1: now this trainer has been fired from the gym and will never be able to work at another gym ( virgin active ) ever again.
the point of me telling this story is to encourage and empower other woman to stand up and not keep quiet. and a lot of us do
column3: but because it's the easiest thing to do.

column1: well i say no more. don't fall victim to any man. and if you are a man and it happened to you and you feel victimized
column2: don't keep quiet. no matter what gender you are

column1: no man or woman should ever be a victim to sexual harassment.

column1: i recently had the opportunity to attend the mit disobedience awards and witness @taranajaneen
column3: receive an award for her dedication to calling out injustice
column4: most specifically around sexual assault. however
column5: on stage with her were five other award recipients and they were all badass women.

column1: i left the even feeling inspired and ready to take on the world. moreover
column2: i was reminded that in order to to live up to the standards i have for myself

column1: if someone is not interested in you
if someone is not messaging you for long hours or days
if someone doesn't care about your feelings
if someone doesn't care to call you
if their behavior changed and they pulled away
if someone is not making plans to see you
inconsistent behavior should be enough closure for you.
i was messaging with a client last night that was struggling.
i woke up inspired to write this.
he can't get enough of you.
he makes plans to see you.
he asks when he can see you frequently.
you feel on top of the world!
you go back to look at text to see what you said that could have been interpreted wrong.
you replay the last times you saw and talk to him and think of what you could have said that made him pull away.
there is nothing wrong with us and our way of love.
it simply doesn't match with their way of loving.
we have different ways to love that is not in alignment with how they love.

this is a sign from the universe that he isn't for you. he was just passing by to send you this message ""you need to find someone that loves how you love. you need to find someone that will give you love in the way you need to receive it to feel loved (hint: 5 love languages).""
you date to see if you get the feeling you are looking for.
this is where so many women get into toxic relationships.
you stay because you want to change them.

(this is called a hip escape) *make just enough room that you can bring both your feet in-between you and your attacker.
2) using the same foot you used to help you scoot out of the way
column2: (hip escape) place that foot on their hip. this will help you keep
column3: maintain distance and set up your kick to their face with your free foot. (use your heel when kicking

column1: 3) after you kick your attacker in the face (aim for the nose) we need to posture up on the same side elbow we used to kick. *please notice how my other hand is at all times framing/shielding my face
column2: just in case they decided to keep striking*

column1: 4) place the foot you had on their hips on the floor and push yourself up from your elbow all the way to your hand and bring your hips up. (this will help you do the next step)

column2: with the same foot you used to kick
column3: bring that knee back and place it by your hand. now get up into your self-defense stance.

column1: hi ladies! just wanted to remind you that this is the last month to submit your story/poem if you are interested in being included in my #metoo book.

if you need a refresher on the project or you missed my posts about it before here‚Äôs some info. ‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è my latest project is called ‚Äú#metoo: a collection of true story crimes against women.‚Äù

the book will be a collection of true story experiences written in women‚Äôs own words. these poems and stories will chronicle the crimes and the effects that the experiences had on each woman. üîú stories and poems will be accepted until december 31
if you have a story/poem that you would like to include email me at mchillstromauthor@yahoo.com.
all stories/poems will be listed as anonymous submissions. ‚û°Ô∏èthe types of stories i am looking for include personal experiences of:
-i will accept other topics if they fit in with the theme as well. üî¥ through writing about my own experiences i have found peace and strength.

i hope others will find this as well and that the future readers of this collection will find courage and strength in the knowledge that they are not alone. üí≤ proceeds from the sales of this collection will be donated to help sexual assault survivors. üî¥ also within the book there will be a section  crediting tarana burke for creating the me too movement and detailing the growth of the movement over the last decade.

let‚Äôs start with this photo.  back in april while jumping in the shower i saw really beautiful shadows coming through the blinds. i set up my iphone on a self timer and took an impromptu photo shoot.  since then i have tirelessly debated whether i should post it.  if you didn‚Äôt notice... i‚Äôm naked. nudity for me has always been a topic of contention. in my head
column2: of course. a large portion of instagrams i follow are mostly naked women. i love looking at the female body. it‚Äôs art... plain and simple. every shape

column4: i grew up in church.  i was taught to cover up.  i was taught that women and especially the female body
column5: are temptations to men. i was taught that masturbation is bad.  i was taught to wait for marriage to have sex and that your husband should be the only person to see or feel you. i was taught that you shouldn‚Äôt care about looks.

column3: is that every time i dressed up beautifully... every time i wore a skirt too short... every time i looked in the mirror and liked what i saw.  my guess is that every time
column5: i learned to hate myself a little more.
